            <h3 class="sub-section-title text-center wow fadeInDown">Education</h3>
            <div class="text-center text-justify justified wow fadeInDown">
                <p>
                    Pernankila village has higher literacy rate compared to Karnataka. In 2011, literacy rate of Pernankila village was 82.35 % compared to 75.36 % of Karnataka. In Pernankila Male literacy stands at 88.36 % while female literacy rate was 76.47 %.
                </p>
                <p>
                    There is an anganavadi kendra and a government higher primary school at the center of  the village. For high school education, students needs to go to <b><i>Sri Vishnumoorthy High School</i></b>, Kodibettu which is around 2.5km from Pernankila. To get pre-university and higher education, students travel to Hiriadka, Moodubelle, Manipal or Udupi. Nearest engineering colleges are Nitte and Bantakal.
